  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0dbd\u0dba\u0da7 \u0db8\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dcf \u0dc0\u0dd3 \u0dc0\u0dd0\u0dbb\u0daf\u0dd2 \u0d9a\u0dc5 80\u0d9a\u0dca \u0dbb\u0da7 \u0db4\u0dd0\u0db1\u0dbd\u0dcf",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "80 people who made mistakes under the guise of struggle fled the country",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "According to security sources, around eighty people, including leading businessmen, who were involved in various illegal activities during the struggle, have fled abroad by various means.",
        "These days, the security forces are on a special search for these people who have fled abroad.",
        "The assistance of international security organizations including Interpol has also been sought for their arrest.",
        "It is known that some have gone abroad and submitted false information to the embassies that there are various threats.",
        "According to the security forces, a millionaire businessman who allegedly broke into the presidential palace and took selfies and released them on the internet has fled to Africa.",
        "He fled abroad after the police started investigating the incident.",
        "Meanwhile, it is also reported that nearly 200 other people involved in the struggle have sought asylum in embassies to go abroad.",
        "The police said that they are looking for the arrest of nearly thirty more people in connection with the incidents of trespassing into the Presidential Palace, Araliyagaha Palace and the burning and destruction of Prime Minister Ranil Wickremesinghe's house."
      ],
